summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 21204, entitled, "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Fifth Avenue West, from West Prospect Street, to West Highland Drive, all in the City of Seattle, by constructing concrete sidewalks thereon, all in accordance with Resolution No. 2128 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment" as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle," approved June 23rd, 1909.
